==Chinese==
{{zh-forms|alt=𥻆}}

===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{liushu|p}} in {{w|oracle bone script}}. During the {{w|Warring States period}}, {{Han compound|ls=psc|角|米|c1=p|c2=s|t2=rice|nocap=yes}}. {{lang|zh|角}} corrupted into {{lang|zh|𠧪}}, thus getting the intermediate form [[𥻆]]. Eventually, it was further corrupted into {{lang|zh|西}}.

In ancient times, this character was used to indicate rice kernels with husk, while [[米]] was used to indicate rice without husk.

===Etymology===
Unclear. {{zh-ref|Blench (2010)}} posits a root {{m|und||#tʃɔk}} that connects this word with {{cog|my|ဆပ်||foxtail millet}}, {{cog|duu|chaq||foxtail millet}}, {{cog|hmx-mie-pro|*tjəiᴬ||millet}}, {{cog|tay|basag}}, among others.

